Spent some time reflecting yesterday and thinking about all the things I hope to accomplish in my last year in my 30’s! I thought about so many things I could list, but when I really examined my heart, I decided that I’m just SO GRATEFUL. 😌 Everything I would have listed when I was 19, I have now. I know what’s important to me and so my list is short: for an even more awakened soul and more gratitude for this next trip around the sun. 🫶🏼 Thank you God for everything you have trusted me with, and thank you all for your love and kindness yesterday on my 39th birthday! James 1:17… #birthday #happybirthday #bestday #almost40 #yikes

On this night, seventeen years ago, you paraded me around a room full of people you knew and introduced me as your “girlfriend”… even though we hadn’t had that conversation yet. 🤔 Kinda like how that at home gym showed up at our house today and we hadn’t talked about that either… yeah, like that. 🫠 As they say, the rest is history and you’ve been holding me hostage ever since. You’re the best dad, you’re loyal as the day is long, and you make sure to always keep us laughing (even when you know it’s pissing me off). Sometimes I can’t believe this all started with social media, an airplane ticket, and a blind date, but I guess we will save that story for another day. Happy you + me day, Champ. ❤️ (swipe for our first ever pic together which weirdly looks similar to pics we took in november!)

The weight of what Easter means didn’t really hit me until I was an adult in my mid/late twenties. This morning, our Pastor read Romans 10:8 and it was exactly what I needed this Easter. 🙌🏼 We don’t have to have it all together. We don’t have to have perfect church attendance. We don’t have to have the most money, work the hardest, be the most patient parent, or have the longest quiet times. It means that if we believe that Jesus Christ died for our sins, and that God raised him from the dead, that we are made right with God. PERIOD. Nothing more. Nothing less. ✝️🤍 and in case no one has ever told you: you are loved more than you could ever fathom by a God who died to know you! 🫶🏼🫶🏼 Happy Easter, gram fam. HE IS ALIVE! 🥳🥳

I don’t ever share pics or videos of my workouts anymore, but that’s mainly because I’m usually in a hurry to get it done and my garage isn’t “pretty”. 🙄 But here’s the “workout secret” I live by: DO NOT COMPLICATE IT. Get outside, get your heart rate up, get your sweat on, do some light weights if you have them, and if not use your body! I borrowed my kids bike and got in a quick 5 miles that took me about 30 mins. Strength training immediately after (in my ugly, but very normal garage) with some dumbbells and then some stretching. Total workout time: 50 mins. I don’t focus on perfection (my form sucks and my plans are all over the place). But I do think in terms of progress! 🫶🏼💪🏽
